Sentencas: Anode aluminum oxide-supported thin-film fuel cells having a sub-500-nm-thick bilayered electrolyte comprising a gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) layer and an yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) layer were fabricated and electrochemically characterized in order to investigate the effect of the YSZ protective layer.
Titulo: Fabrication of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with a nanothin protective layer by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: The highly dense and thin YSZ layer acted as a blockage against electron and oxygen permeation between the anode and GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with a nanothin protective layer by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: Dense GDC and YSZ thin films were fabricated using radio frequency sputtering and atomic layer deposition techniques, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with a nanothin protective layer by atomic layer deposition

Sentencas: The resulting bilayered thin-film fuel cell generated a significantly higher open circuit voltage of approximately 1.07 V compared with a thin-film fuel cell with a single-layered GDC electrolyte (approximately 0.3 V).
Titulo: Fabrication of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with a nanothin protective layer by atomic layer deposition
